A study shows that the longer officers stay in the police service the more isolated they become from the public. CAPE TOWN While police are almost always at the receiving end of negative criticism, they happen to be equally cynical of the public. A recent study headed by Dr Jean Steyn, academic leader for Criminology at the University of KwaZulu-Natal, shows that the longer you stay in the police service the more isolated you become from the public.Steyn talks to Cape Talk s Kienno Kammies about the ways these views may affect policing in the country.